&nbsp;AGI - The president of the Palestinian National Authority, Abu Mazen>, said that he "will review" his bilateral relations with the United States after the veto placed by Washington at the full entry of Palestine in the United Nations" in order to ensure the protection of the interests of our people, our cause and our rights". The Palestinian agency Wafa reports it.
&nbsp;
Israeli Foreign Minister Israel Katz, criticized Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan> for meeting in Istanbul the leader of the Hamas political office, Ismail Haniyeh>. "The alliance of the Muslim Brotherhood: rapes, murders, destruction of bodies and burned children," wrote Katz in a post on X, posting a photo of Erdogan and Haniyeh holding hands. "Vergognati, Erdogan!", added.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The meeting between Erdogan and Haniyeh lasted over two and a half hours. Face to face, initially planned in Ankara but then staged at Dolmabahce Palace in Istanbul, also took part in the former number one of Hamas, Khaled Meshal>, the head of Turkish intelligence, Ibrahim Kalin>, and Turkish Foreign Minister Hakan Fidan>. The representatives of Turkey and Hamas discussed the humanitarian situation in Gaza, the difficulties of delivering humanitarian aid to the civilian population, but above all the possibility of a ceasefire with Israel and the increasing tensions between the Jewish State and Iran, one of the main allies of the Palestinian organization.
&nbsp;
The Turkish President defined "vital" the unity of the Palestinians against Israel and reiterated that without the solution of the two States peace remains "impossible". "To be united is the strongest answer to Israel. The beginning of a path that leads to victory lies in the unity and integrity of the people. Israel will pay for the crimes committed", reads in a statement of the Turkish presidency.&nbsp;
11 Palestinians in the West Bank
While in the Gaza Strip the number of victims of the conflict would have exceeded 34 thousand, violence continues to invest also the West Bank, where ten "Palestinian soldiers", according to Israel, were killed in the West Bank during a raid in Nur Shams, a refugee camp, by the Israeli security forces. "The security forces have eliminated 10 terrorists during the clashes," which lasted over 40 hours, tells the Israeli army. Eight soldiers and a police officer were injured. According to testimonies from the refugee camp, an interruption of electricity occurred and food is scarce but no one can go out or enter the camp. According to the official Palestinian sources, from the beginning of the conflict on October 7, some 480 Palestinians were killed by Israeli troops or settlers in the West Bank.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp; A 50-year-old Palestinian, an ambulance driver, was also killed by gunfire while evacuating wounded during a confrontation between Palestinians and settlers in As-Sawiya, south of Nablus in West Bank. He denounced the ministry of health of Ramallah.

